name: <-o-°-[___]-°-o->
description:
if I squint my eyes hard enough, 
will I find the way back? 
---------------------------------------

A thank you to all current (15.02.22) holders of one of the girlsGAN.gifs (OBJKT#671021,#670950,#670939). 
 
This sequence was constructed from the latent space of a test training with 732 stills from 43 Russian films {1908-15}. The category of this data set is "Landscapes (with people)". My understanding of landscape here is extremely broad and would be better described as exterior shots, so I might end up splitting this data set for my film.

In contrast to what I could find through the data set I used for girlsGAN.gif, the colours I find here are not as intense and mostly a variety of blueish-grey and beige-orange, often resembling winter or cold sunrises. For this sequence I also chose more abstract scenes reminiscent of landscapes and less those with vertical figures.

(For a few more infos about my currently ongoing Experimental Film project see "girlsGAN.gif (1)", OBJKT#671021)
